OL,5,CInquiry
OL,7,FMr Poole said the agreed with the
OL,8,Fdecision to use public health rules,
OL,9,Fwhich would allow Wales to "reflect
OL,10,Fthe particular circumstances" of the
OL,11,Fcountry, but the UK Government's
OL,12,Fdecision was "not formally made until
OL,13,FMarch 20".
OL,15,FProf Wincott agreed had assumed any
OL,16,F"primary decision-making power" would
OL,17,Fremain with the UK Government.
OL,19,F"That certainly seems to be the
OL,20,Funderstanding of the situation," he
OL,21,Fsaid.
